THIS CASE WAS SPUN TO JUDGE CONEN FROM JUDGE POCAN'S COURT.

Defendant Bryan Sanders in court with Attorney Ann T. Bowe.  Defendant Bryan Sanders in custody.  James C. Griffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter here for a sentencing hearing.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

AS TO COUNT #1:    The Court imposed the following sentence:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be ELEVEN (11) years CONCURRENT to any other sentence.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for FOUR (4) years with credit for TWENTY (20) days time served.  Defendant shall serve SEVEN (7) years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.

The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol; Absolute sobriety;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - No contact with the victim, Radio Shack, or co-actors, Trevante Young and Trevor Young;
 - The defendant has to receive his Bachelor's Degree; 
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements.  The Court ordered monies taken by the Department of Correction from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balance would be then be paid while on Extended Supervision.  If not paid by end of extended supervision, the balance would convert to a civil judgment.

A restitution hearing will be held on December 15, 2015 at 8:30am in Br. 30, Judge Conen's court.

Filed,
